The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Braithwaite bailout in the works

 Calcutta, July 10 (PTI): The Centre is considering a Rs 288-crore restructuring package for Braithwaite, said heavy industries and public enterprises minister Santosh Mohan Dev. 

 The Board for Reconstruction of Public Sector Enterprises has approved the revival proposal for three firms under Bharat Bhari Udyog Nigam Ltd ? BBJ, Braithwaite and Bharat Wagon. 

 The Union cabinet has also approved the recommendation of the board in case of BBJ, following which the government has approved a revival proposal of Rs 55 crore for the company, said Dev while inaugurating the arc furnaces of Braithwaite in Hooghly.

 He added that the proposal for the revival of Burn Standard is being finalised by Bharat Bhari Udyog in consultation with the administrative ministry. 




